Model selection matrix (revised):
- < 8 GB RAM, no GPU: qwen3:0.6b (~400MB)
- 8-16 GB RAM, no GPU: qwen3:1.7b (~1.4GB)
- 16+ GB RAM, no GPU: qwen3:8b (~5GB)
- GPU 4-8 GB VRAM: qwen3:8b (~5GB)
- GPU 8-16 GB VRAM: 14B class model
- GPU 16+ GB VRAM: largest available (20B+)

The installer detects GPU VRAM and selects accordingly. The selected model is pulled during install and set as rank 1 in provider_priority.

First-load notification: Local models take 30-90 seconds to load from disk into GPU/RAM on first use after restart. The platform must:
1. Detect when a cold-load is happening (first inference after model was unloaded)
2. Show a clear notification: "Loading AI model into memory... this takes about a minute on first use"
3. Show progress or at least an animated indicator so the user knows it is working
4. After first load, set keep_alive=-1 so the model stays in memory

The weekly optimization agent should also factor in cold-load time when ranking local providers.
